Which one is correct, you can only choose one of the options, the question is:[How can you use your literature review question to focus your review effectively??]The options are:[ Set the review question only after you have reviewed all available literature;

Ensure your review question defines the scope of your review and the terms used;

Use the review question as a guide but do not use it to structure your review;

Explore the review question only when you write up your review].

Which one is correct, you can only choose one of the options, the question is:[A researcher has been asked to contribute to an edited collection of scientific chapters. What should he do??]The options are:[ Write in the first person and include plenty of personal opinion;

Follow all guidelines and ensure that his writing is based on sound methodology;

Avoid jargon to ensure his writing can be easily understood by a lay audience;

Ignore guidelines so that his writing is unique and individual].

Which one is correct, you can only choose one of the options, the question is:[A researcher has been asked to contribute to an edited collection of scientific chapters. What should he do??]The options are:[  

Write about it on social media to make everyone aware of the situation;

Ignore it: other researchers will know that they are the author of the work;

Register for a unique ORCID identifier and ensure that it is attached to all their research outputs].

Which one is correct, you can only choose one of the options, the question is:[Which of the following statements most accurately reflects the kind of supervisory model a doctoral candidate might expect??]The options are:[
How supervision is arranged will vary, but in many cases candidates work with more than one supervisor;

Candidates will always have at least two supervisors, often more;

Candidates can always expect to have a panel or committee of supervisors;

Candidates only have one main supervisor].
